NFHighlightLayerCollection.html#resetExp.name: resetExpressionErrors
NFHighlightLayerCollection.html#resetExp.description: Reset expression error status for all highlights. This is to be called after #fixExpressionAfterInit. Because of the way AE handles scripting, if a script breaks an expression, then even if it fixes it, the expression error will be there when the script finishes. This just clears that. If there's still an expression error after the script finishes, that'll still appear.
